p: According to prevalent SNPs, all genomes have been classified by amino acid changes in specific ORFs. For the Chilean strains, the first three cases (20‐18918, 20‐19303, 20‐19305) are classified as “S” type, meanwhile, the fourth case (20‐19731) is a “G” type, according to nucleotide substitutions in the positions 28 144 and 23 403, respectively.
